   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-a" mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>You siphon off the weapons?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>The most vicious rumor surrounding <FONT color=#a82424>blacksmiths</FONT> is that we make undue profit and siphon off weapons during strengthening.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-b" mid="14"><![CDATA[<html>Then, how do you get rid of broken weapons?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="12"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>Well, the rumor is like this. We say it's broken during strengthening, but actually we siphon off the weapon behind…. Think about it! There' s nothing like this harmful baseless rumor!</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-b" image="QN_Npc_Saint_BlackSmith_Dwarf.dds" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-c" mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>(Ability? You can fix at general store as well…)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>I'll let you know. In fact, it's hard to fix high level weapons. First, the ability of blacksmith has to be outstanding…<BR>
<FONT color=#7e12d2>(Berlin praises his skill.)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-d" mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>What hammer do you use?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>When you fix weapons, need to keep the extremely high temperature of the kiln. Plus, don't hammer the weapons with an ordinary hammer.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-d" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-e" mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>Do you know you use diamonds to deal with diamond? To fix the high level weapons like that, you gotta use the hammer which has the same level with the weapons.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-e" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-f" mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="22"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>It breaks often, even if you use the hammer made of that high purity iron. Have to make new hammers regularly.<BR>
So I recycle the broken weapons during strengthening as a hammer.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-f" image="" itemindex="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-g" mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>(This may be the real purpose…)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>A picture is worth a thousand words. Just in time, the hammer for Epic loots has broken, help me fix it.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-g" image="QS_Default.dds" itemindex="300325">
      <talk_answer link_index="n091_trader_bellin-accepting-h" mid="28"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="27"><![CDATA[<html>$Blacksmith Berlin$<BR>There are enough broken Epic loots, we need powerful fire to melt them. For the powerful flame <FONT color=#a82424>Fire Elf's Powder</FONT> is good.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
